- 'Eloquently written' refers to reviews with more than 50 words;
- 'More than two' refers to the condition that the count of such reviews for a product must be greater than 2.

- "Top 3 rated products in each category" refers to the highest average ratings within each product category;
- "Positive sentiment" is defined as the sentiment score, which is the difference between the total positive and negative sentiments, being greater than zero;
- "More likes than dislikes" means the total number of likes for the product's reviews is greater than the total number of dislikes.

- "Shining star" refers to the product with the highest average rating;
- "Constellation of reviews" refers to the set of all products and their reviews;
- "More reviews than the average" means the product has a total review count greater than the average total review count across all products.
